This paper deals with approximate inference in probabilistic models, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence and machine learning. The use of Monte Carlo Tree Search and value functions is a reinforcement learning technique, which suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.AI sub-category. The paper also deals with probabilistic inference, which is a topic in both cs.LG and cs.DS. The use of neural networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.PL sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with decision-making under uncertainty, which is a topic in the cs.SY sub-category.
